body:
@jherico GLFW now exposes all mirroring monitors. The display device name of a monitor is now exposed, as UTF-8, by the `glfwGetWin32Monitor` function.

A function, potentially called `glfwGetMirroredMonitor`, will be added to allow applications to detect (and reject) mirroring monitors.

Video mode setting is per mirroring set, as it implicitly was before, and existing mirroring sets are not dissolved by GLFW.
